\title{Using Gh Cli}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{"Guides usage of the GitHub CLI (gh) for interacting with GitHub repositories, PRs, issues, and API. Use when working with GitHub resources instead of WebFetch or curl."}

\subtree{
\title{Using the GitHub CLI (\code{\startverb gh\stopverb})}
\subtree{
\title{When to Use}
\ul{
\li{\strong{Browsing or reading code} from a GitHub repository — clone it and use Read/Glob/Grep}
\li{Viewing or creating pull requests, issues, releases, or gists}
\li{Fetching repo metadata or any GitHub API data}
\li{Interacting with GitHub Actions (runs, workflows)}
\li{Any task involving GitHub that you might otherwise use \code{\startverb curl\stopverb}, \code{\startverb wget\stopverb}, or \code{\startverb WebFetch\stopverb} for}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{When NOT to Use}
\ul{
\li{Non-GitHub URLs (use \code{\startverb WebFetch\stopverb} or \code{\startverb curl\stopverb} for those)}
\li{Public web content that happens to be hosted on GitHub Pages (\code{\startverb *.github.io\stopverb}) — those are regular websites}
\li{Local git operations (\code{\startverb git commit\stopverb}, \code{\startverb git push\stopverb}) — use \code{\startverb git\stopverb} directly}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Key Principle}
\p{\strong{Always use \code{\startverb gh\stopverb} instead of \code{\startverb curl\stopverb}, \code{\startverb wget\stopverb}, or \code{\startverb WebFetch\stopverb} for GitHub URLs.} The \code{\startverb gh\stopverb} CLI uses the user's authenticated token automatically, so it:}

\ul{
\li{Works with private repositories}
\li{Avoids GitHub API rate limits (unauthenticated: 60 req/hr; authenticated: 5,000 req/hr)}
\li{Handles pagination correctly}
\li{Provides structured output and filtering}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Browsing Repository Code}
\p{\strong{To read or browse files from a GitHub repo, clone it locally and use normal file tools} (Read, Glob, Grep). This is much faster and more natural than fetching files one-by-one via the API.}

\pre{\startverb
# Clone to a session-scoped temp directory (cleaned up automatically on session end)
clonedir="$TMPDIR/gh-clones-${CLAUDE_SESSION_ID}"
mkdir -p "$clonedir"
gh repo clone owner/repo "$clonedir/repo" -- --depth 1
\stopverb}

\p{After cloning, use the \strong{Explore agent} (via the Task tool with \code{\startverb subagent_type=Explore\stopverb}) to investigate the cloned repo. The Explore agent can use Read, Glob, and Grep across the clone efficiently — much better than calling them one at a time:}

\pre{\startverb
Task(subagent_type="Explore", prompt="In $clonedir/repo/, find how authentication is implemented")
\stopverb}

\p{For targeted lookups on a clone you already understand, use Read/Glob/Grep directly.}

\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb gh repo clone\stopverb} uses the user's authenticated token — works with private repos}
\li{\code{\startverb --depth 1\stopverb} keeps the clone fast (only latest commit)}
\li{No cleanup needed — a SessionEnd hook removes the clone directory automatically}
\li{Use \code{\startverb gh api\stopverb} only when you need a quick single-file lookup without cloning}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Quick Start}
\pre{\startverb
# View a repo
gh repo view owner/repo

# List and view PRs
gh pr list --repo owner/repo
gh pr view 123 --repo owner/repo

# List and view issues
gh issue list --repo owner/repo
gh issue view 456 --repo owner/repo

# Call any REST API endpoint
gh api repos/owner/repo/contents/README.md

# Call with pagination and jq filtering
gh api repos/owner/repo/pulls --paginate --jq '.[].title'
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Common Patterns}
\pre{\startverb
| Instead of | Use |
|------------|-----|
| `WebFetch` on `github.com/owner/repo` | `gh repo view owner/repo` |
| `WebFetch` on a blob/tree URL | Clone with `gh repo clone` and use Read/Glob/Grep |
| `WebFetch` on `raw.githubusercontent.com/...` | Clone with `gh repo clone` and use Read |
| `WebFetch` on `api.github.com/...` | `gh api <endpoint>` |
| `curl https://api.github.com/...` | `gh api <endpoint>` |
| `curl` with `-H "Authorization: token ..."` | `gh api <endpoint>` (auth is automatic) |
| `wget` to download a release asset | `gh release download --repo owner/repo` |
\stopverb}
}

